    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">[London, Ont.,]<ptr target="syr.00049_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1889-04-02">2 April [188]9</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Your card of 31<hi rend="underline">st</hi> just to hand.<ptr target="syr.00049_n2"/>
                Very sorry to hear such bad accounts of the cold but trust it will soon be better,
                [/] wish you could have a good alcohol bath, real good sweat, would help you very
                much&#8212;can you not get some one in Camden to help you to arrange an alcohol
                bath&#8212;it is extremely simple. Willy Gurd<ptr target="n4284"/> still here, he
                goes East tomorrow morning, has the gas meter<ptr target="syr.00049_n3"/> all
                constructed ("in his minds eye") already, will soon put it together when he gets
                alongside his lathe&#8212;all well here and nothing new. Ground still quite white
                with snow</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately yours</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
